{
  "texts": [
    "It can be concluded that G&O is more suited for LLMs that are designed with a focus on reasoning abilities and the capacity to engage in multi-round conversations.",
    "In our study on RE, we evaluate 3 datasets: CoNLL 2004 (Roth and Yih, 2004), NYT (Zeng et al., 2018), and PolyIE.",
    "Our RE approach is end-toend, predicting entities and their relations within the same iteration, which mirrors real-world scenarios and presents a greater challenge.",
    "We primarily assess G&O-RE against the One-Step method using GPT-3.5, focusing on partial and full match precision, recall, and F 1 scores.",
    "Elaboration on G&O-RE is provided in appendix A.4."
  ]
}